Customize Labels and Translations for the Channel Menu

Use our existing default labels or create custom labels for your menu header and channel names. Additional steps are required to set any label translations.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Channel Menu setup node is available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Performance, Professional, Unlimited, and Essentials


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To set up Channel Menu:	Customize Application AND Modify Metadata

Here’s a side-by-side comparison of a Channel Menu before and after light branding. The button and header background colors were changed in Branding. The Header text and Menu Item text was changed in Labels.

From the main Channel Menu Settings page, select Edit for Labels to customize your menu labels. To change your default names:

Select All in the Label Group and Standard in Label Type.
Enter your custom label text for each default label.
Save your work before moving to a new Label Group or Label Type.
Your updated labels appear in the Preview window.
Click Finish.

If you don’t see the language you need in the Language picklist for your labels, complete the following steps in Translation Workbench:

From Setup, enter Translations Language Settings in the Quick Find box.
Enable the Translation Workbench.
Add languages for translation and activate by checking the checkbox.
Assign the language to the user by moving from the Available to Selected box.
Add the user language as a translatable language.

IMPORTANT The admin must authorize a logged-in user in a specific language to translate labels. Then, the user can customize the words or phrases.
title: Customizing Channel Menu Labels and Translations
